<br>
But, I do have to express the sort of displeasure I see from Magicians getting a nuke at level 61, that outclasses all wizard nukes of the last 4 years in 1 level.  Mainly level 60 though, the level that has been *the* pedestal level of the wizard class.  A level 1-59 wizard is nothing compared to a level 60 wizard.  And as a guildleader of a high level raiding guild, I can tell you I would never let a wizard into my guild until he got 60.  While, atleast before the rod nerf, I was letting mages in at 58 just for extra mod rods and the rarity of mages.<br>
<br>
But thats sort of off subject.  Basically, one, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Firebolt of Tallon</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> outclasses almost every single level 60 wizard nuke in every way.  Yes, I understand the line of sight constraints, but from my experience with good mages, that is hardly an issue.  Also, considering it has a better ratio and dps then <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Garrison's Superior Sundering</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> which is the nuke of Luclin.  A spell that only drops off the Emperor of Ssra.  A vast majority of wizards will most likely never see this spell.  While it doesn't have the greatest mana ratio of level 60 wizard spells, it's DPS was the highest for it's wide usage.  <br>
<br>
The one real wizard spell that matchs in efficency is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ice Spear of Solist</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, which is probably the most common level 60 wizard spell of today.  It does have a 4.0 ratio of efficency, but with the 13 second recast time, the dps is extremely lacking.  And as we know, dps is what the wizard class is about.<br>
<br>
Now there are a few exceptions to the spell line up.  We can look at <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Porlo's Fury</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->(Dragonsbane), <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Hsarga's Wraith</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->(Giantsbane), and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ancient: Destruction of Ice</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->; which all have exceptional ratios of ~4.4 for DB/GB and 4.8 for DoI.  But you have to consider the rarity and usage of these spells.  The Ancient spell is quite obvious, but if you compare it to the mage Ancient spell, there really isn't comparison overall.  While Giantsbane is fairly easy to obtain with faction, it only works on a grand total of 3 or 4 mobs and has extremely high aggro.  Dragonsbane is definitly a class defining spell that really only works in ToV for the most part.  But you have to consider the exceptional rarity in obtaining it.  It is even worse than Sunstrike.  <br>
<br>
Overall when you consider level 60 wizard spells, you have to consider rartiy.<br>
<br>
* Ice Spear of Solist - Semi-Common Velious boss mob drop.  <br>
* Sunstrike - Very Rare Kunark Level 60+ Drop.  Torpor style rare.<br>
* Elernick's Electrical Rendering - Semi-Common drop off a tough Luclin mob.<br>
* Garrison's Superior Sundering - Common drop off an extremely tough luclin mob.<br>
* Ancient: Destruction of Ice - Random Rare drop from the tough RoV event.<br>
* Giantsbane - Easy to obtain, extremely limited usage, costs 2 peridots to cast.<br>
* Dragonsbane - Very rare quest mob (Myga) that drops a piece to get this spell, worse then sunstrike, costs 2 peridots to cast.<br>
<br>
Basically, when you look over the spells, you'll see wizards have been fighting hard for their nukes for a long time.  But VI never seems to let up on them in any expansion.  I can safely say, that Strike of Solusek, will probably be a horribly painful spell to obtain.  While I bet the Draught line will be vendor bought. <br>
<br>
If you look at Mage nuke history, you'll find that your nukes are relatively easy to obtain.  <br>
<br>
And considering all this, 1 level later, Mages have a nuke that has probably the best Combo of DPS + Mana Ratio over wizard spells that will most likely be a common drop or a vendor bought spell.  <br>
<br>
You have to consider that, and that is why, I feel that the balance of the spells is slightly out of wack.  Now, in my personal opinion, if they added a Draught spell or a wizard equavilant nuke for wizards at 61, then I'm sure alot of wizards would be all fine and dandy.  Otherwise, I too agree that moving the spell up a level or 2 would make alot more sense.  <p><HR Width="25%" Align="Left">
